text: Ivana Plchotová (born 30 October 1982) is a Czech volleyball player. She played at the 2007 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2009 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2011 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2013 Women's European Volleyball Championship, and 2015–16 CEV Women's Champions League. She played for MKS Dąbrowa Górnicza and CS Volei Alba Blaj. == References == Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Czech volleyball players
